Lucy Njoki Njuki

I am Lucy Njoki Njuki, currently employed as a Research Assistant at the Centre for Epidemiology VS Arthritis at the University of Manchester. I will soon be assuming the role of Data Analyst at the University of Oxford. Simultaneously, I am pursuing my MSc in Statistics and Data Science (Biostatistics) as a part-time second-year student at Hasselt University through a distance learning program. Alongside my academic pursuits, I actively contribute to the R community and serve as an organiser for R-Ladies Nairobi chapter.

Talks

In this section, I present the collection of talks I have delivered thus far throughout my early career as a researcher.

  1. Speaker | R User Group University of Manchester | R.U.M - Publication Ready Tables - User-defined functions to create summary tables | Resources

  2. Regular speaker| Shiny Conference 2023 | Making Project Management Seemless | Resources | Recording

  3. Panellist | Shiny Conference 2022 | Women in Shiny with R-Ladies | Recording

  4. Guest speaker | NamibiaR Launch Event | Slides

  5. Keynote speaker | R-Ladies Gaborone Launch Event | Slides | Recording

  6. Presenter | Modelling Risk Factors of Oesophagus Cancer, Case Study of Nairobi County, 2009 2011 | 1st University of Nairobi International Biostatistics Conference

Trainings

This section lists the trainings I have done plus resources to reproduce what I trained.

Microblogs
